Wipro’s Premji Invests $15 Million in Khosla’s Clean-Tech Fund, Times Says

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-05-16T01:14:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/wipro-s-premji-invests-15-million-in-khosla-s-clean-tech-fund-times-says.html
Azim Premji, chairman of  Wipro Ltd. (WPRO) ,
 India ’s third-largest software-services provider, has invested
$15 million in billionaire Vinod Khosla’s clean-tech fund for
his first overseas investment, the Economic Times reported,
citing people it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
